-- GM U.S. May sales plunge 30 percent
-- 
-- Tue Jun 3, 2008 3:31pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/06/03/us-gm-sales-us-idUSWNAS671420080603

 

 DETROIT  (Reuters) - General Motors Corp on Tuesday reported a 30.2 percent fall in May U.S. auto sales on an adjusted basis, led by a 39 percent decline in truck sales. 

 GM's overall sales fell to 272,363 vehicles in May from 375,682 in the same month a year earlier. (Reporting by  Poornima Gupta ; editing by John Wallace)